name: ticket-system
description: An example of a microservice monorepo project using a multi-module Go workspace. Features Docker for containerization, Kafka as a message broker, and PostgreSQL as the database.

name: auth-system
description: A complete authentication system microservice for a social media platform.

name: Istio-Kubernetes-Services-Mesh-Microservices
description: Studies based in day 7-8 of 100 Days System Design for DevOps and Cloud Engineers

name: Project-Management-System
description: Microservices-based project using Spring Boot, Java 17, and MySQL including services for user management, project management, project submission, and an API gateway.

name: Auction-App
description: Auction Platform is a scalable, microservices system for car auctions. Built with ASP.NET Core, and Next.js. Deployed and containerized using Docker, Kubernetes, and DigitalOcean.

name: StudentAdminMgmtSys
description: This repository contains a microservices-based School Administration Management System built with Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, and PostgreSQL. It includes services for admin, teacher, and student management, enabling functionalities such as managing student information, study materials, notices, and complaints. This system leverages Eureka.

name: Report-As-A-Service
description: This project is a comprehensive report generation system that offers two approaches: Next.js Server-Side Rendering (SSR) and Microservices Architecture. It provides dynamic report generation with the option to display reports as HTML web content or generate downloadable PDF documents. The system also supports robust data visualization using ECharts

name: Bus-Booking-Application
description: A scalable, non-blocking microservices-based application that enables users to book and cancel long-distance bus reservations. The system handles real-time seat availability and booking confirmation, integrating various services such as user registration, scheduling, booking, and notification processing.
